hich tend to be pronounced as [guɹeɪtə] by Mandarin speakers. %0a%3c %0a%3c From these examples, we can see that the consonant cluster of an obstruent followed by a sonorant seem unnatural to Mandarin speakers and require insertion of a vowel to break them up. Furthermore, we see that [ə] is added after velar and alveolar plosives, while [u] is added after bilabial plosives /p/ and /b/.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
